parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine bucking or misfire issue can cause a loss of power, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially lead to engine damage or failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine intermittently bucks or misfires
particularly at specific RPMs (e.g.
250 RPM) and speeds (e.g.
55 MPH)
the check engine light appears
the vehicle may experience a loss of power or hesitation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument gauge cluster illumination can cause difficulty in reading critical vehicle information, such as speed, fuel level, and engine performance, which can lead to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: The instrument gauge cluster does not illuminate all the gauges
some gauges are dim or do not light up
bulbs burning out frequently
multiple repair attempts do not resolve the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Bulb Failure in Instrument Gauge Cluster
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The frequent burning out of bulbs in the instrument gauge cluster can cause difficulty in reading critical vehicle information, leading to safety issues.
symptoms: Bulbs burning out frequently
instrument gauge cluster does not illuminate all the gauges
some gauges are dim or do not light up.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Front Running Light and/or Light Defect Indicator
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty front running light can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions. The persistent "Light Defect" dashboard warning can be distracting and may lead to driver frustration.
symptoms: The front running light fails to illuminate
the light flickers or dims
the "Light Defect" dashboard warning remains on even after repair
the light may turn on and off intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the electronic seat memory can cause inconvenience and discomfort to the driver and passengers, as they may need to readjust the seat settings frequently.
symptoms: The seat memory function fails to recall the stored settings
the seat settings are not retained
the seat moves unexpectedly
the seat does not adjust to the desired position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty seat control module can cause the electronic seat memory to malfunction, leading to inconvenience and discomfort for the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The seat memory function fails to recall the stored settings
the seat settings are not retained
the seat moves unexpectedly
the seat does not adjust to the desired position.
